@startuml
title FIG-23-01. Choosing the Right Decision and Business-Rule Artefact
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F5F7FA
  BorderColor #333333
  FontColor #111111
  RoundCorner 10
}
left to right direction
rectangle "Start with the\ndecision question" as Start #DCEAF7
rectangle "Policy statement or\nKnowledge Source" as Policy
rectangle "Decision table" as Table
rectangle "Decision tree" as Tree
rectangle "DMN Decision\nRequirements Diagram" as DRD
rectangle "BPMN process view" as BPMN
rectangle "Architecture\nDecision Record" as ADR
rectangle "Trade-off matrix" as Matrix
rectangle "Clarify decision,\naudience and evidence" as Clarify #FFF2CC
Start --> Policy : What authority\nconstrains behaviour?
Start --> Table : Which condition combinations\nproduce which result?
Start --> Tree : Which ordered questions\nlead to a result?
Start --> DRD : What information and knowledge\ndoes the decision require?
Start --> BPMN : What work happens before\nor after the result?
Start --> ADR : Why was an architecture\noption chosen?
Start --> Matrix : How do alternatives compare\nagainst explicit criteria?
Start --> Clarify : Still unclear?
note bottom of Start
  When several questions apply,
  create separate linked artefacts.
end note
@enduml
